<subSubSection id="11FDD8C4347005A95E42876979AA4125" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7000BA7354AD11FF7B3E31E553B862FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="960471371554BC09A1465CFFB3D7E57A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
4.5-4.8 mm long (4.7 mm long; n = 3); 2.4-2.5
<normalizedToken id="B2993465FDF18F673A258A64F6BBC890" originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by its large size; pronotum rounded, robust from lateral view (type 5); declivital interstriae 1 unarmed (lacking granules) and flat; declivital strial punctures very large, irregularly spaced; and declivital surface appearing smooth and opalescent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
